controls.control_description:
A bank not complying with provisions of section 11 (1) of the Banking Regulation
Act, 1949 (AACS) is required to obtain prior approval of the Reserve Bank for:
(1) Sale of bank's own premises;

Delivery process
a) Cash collected from the customer should be acknowledged by issuing a receipt
on behalf of the bank;

d) Delivery of demand draft should be done by debit to the account on the basis
of requisition in writing / cheque received and not against cash or instruments
collected at the doorstep;
